obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (4219)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4219&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Extradition Act,`
  line 1962.
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 5th January, 1963, vide Notification No. G.S.R. 55, dated 5th January, 1963, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (4220)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4220&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) "composite offence" means an act or conduct of a person occurred, wholly or in part, in`
  line `a foreign State or in india but its effects or Intended effects, taken as a whole, would constitute an`
  line `extradition offence in India or in a foreign State, as the case may be;]`
  line
  line `(b) "conviction" and "convicted" do not include or refer to a conviction which under foreign`
  line `law is a conviction for contumacy, but the term "person accused" includes a person so convicted`
  line `for contumacy;`
  line
  line `^2[(c) "extradition offence" means--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a foreign State, being a treaty State, an offence provided for in the`
  line `extradition treaty with that State;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a foreign State other than a treaty State an offence punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one year under the laws of India or of a`
  line `foreign State and includes a composite offence;]`
  line
  line `(d) "extradition treaty" means a treaty ^3[,agreement or arrangement) made by India with a`
  line `foreign State relating to the extradition of fugitive criminals, and includes any treaty ^3[,agreement`
  line `or arrangement] relating to the extradition of fugitive criminals made before the 15th day of`
  line `August, 1947, which extends to, and is binding on, India;`
  line
  line `(e) "foreign State" means any State outside India ^4* * * and includes every constituent part,`
  line `colony or dependency of such State;`
  line
  line `^5[(f) "fugitive criminal" means a person who is accused or convicted of an extradition offence`
  line `within the jurisdiction of a foreign State and includes a person who, while in India, conspires,`
  line `attempts to commit or incites or participates as an accomplice in the commission of an extradition`
  line `offence in a foreign State;]`
  line
  line `(g) "magistrate" means a magistrate of the first class or a presidency magistrate;`
  line
  line `(h) "notified order" means an order notified in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(i) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(j) "treaty State" means a foreign State with which an extradition treaty is in operation.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 66 of 1993, s. 4, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f.18-12-1993).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "or agreement" (w.e.f.18-12-1993).`
  line
  line `4. The words "other than a commonwealth country," omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for clause (f) (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (4221)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Application of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4221&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Central Government may, by notified order, direct that the`
  line `provisions of this Act, other than Chapter III, shall apply, to such foreign State or part thereof as may`
  line `be specified in the order.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by the same notified order as is referred to in sub-section (1) or`
  line `any subsequent notified order, restrict such application to fugitive criminals found, or suspected to be,`
  line `in such part of India as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the notified order relates to a treaty State,--`
  line
  line `(a) it shall set out in full the extradition treaty with that State ;`
  line
  line `(b) it shall not remain in force for any period longer than that treaty; and`
  line
  line `(c) the Central Government may, by the same or any subsequent notified order, render the`
  line `application of this Act subject to such modifications, exceptions, conditions and qualifications as`
  line `may be deemed expedient for implementing the treaty with that State.`
  line
  line `^2[(4) Where there is no extradition treaty made by India with any foreign State, the`
  line `Central Government may, by notified order, treat any Convention to which India and a foreign State`
  line `are parties, as an extradition treaty made by India with that foreign State providing for extradition in`
  line `respect of the offences specified in that Convention.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 66 of 1993, s. 5, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (4222)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Requisition for surrender.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4222&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `A requisition for the surrender of a fugitive criminal of a`
  line `foreign State ^1`
  line `* * * may be made to the Central Government--`
  line
  line `(a) by a diplomatic representative of the foreign State ^1`
  line `* * * at Delhi; or`
  line
  line `(b) by the Government of that foreign State ^1`
  line `* * * communicating with the Central`
  line `Government through its diplomatic representative in that State ^2`
  line ***;
  line
  line `and if neither of these modes is convenient, the requisition shall be made in such other mode as is`
  line `settled by arrangement made by the Government of the foreign State ^1`
  line `* * * with the Government of`
  line India.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or commonwealth country" omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f.18-12-1993).`
  line
  line `2. The words "or country" omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (4223)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Order for magisterial inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4223&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Where such requisition is made, the Central Government`
  line `may, if it thinks fit, issue an order to any Magistrate who would have had jurisdiction to inquire into`
  line `the offence if it had been an offence committed within the local limits of his jurisdiction directing him`
  line `to inquire into the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (4224)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Issue of warrant for arrest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4224&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `On receipt of an order of the Central Government under`
  line `section 5, the magistrate shall issue a warrant for the arrest of the fugitive criminal.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (4225)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Procedure before magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. The words "or commonwealth country" omitted by Act 66 of 1993, s. 3 (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4225&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the fugitive criminal appears or is brought before`
  line `the magistrate, the magistrate shall inquire into the case in the same manner and shall have the same`
  line `jurisdiction and powers, as nearly as may be, as if the case were one triable by a court of session or`
  line `High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, the magistrate shall, in`
  line `particular, take such evidence as may be produced in support of the requisition of the foreign State`
  line ^1
  line `* * * and on behalf of the fugitive criminal, including any evidence to show that the offence of which`
  line `the fugitive criminal accused or has been convicted is an offence of political character or is not an`
  line `extradition offence.`
  line
  line `(3) If the Magistrate is of opinion that a prima facie case is not made out in support of the`
  line `requisition of the foreign State ^1`
  line `* * *, he shall discharge the fugitive criminal.`
  line
  line `(4) If the Magistrate is of opinion that a prima facie case is made out in support of the requisition`
  line `of the foreign State ^1`
  line `* * * he may commit the fugitive criminal to prison to await the orders of the`
  line `Central Government and shall report the result of his inquiry to the Central Government, and shall`
  line `forward together with such report, and written statement which the fugitive criminal may desire to`
  line `submit for the consideration of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (4226)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Surrender of fugitive criminal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. The words "or commonwealth country" omitted by Act 66 of 1993, s. 3 (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4226&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `If upon receipt of the report and statement under subsection (4) of section 7, the Central Government is of opinion that the fugitive criminal ought to be`
  line `surrendered to the foreign State ^1`
  line `* * *, it may issue a warrant for the custody and removal of the`
  line `fugitive criminal and for his delivery at a place and to a person to be named in the warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (4227)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power of magistrate to issue warrant of arrest in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. The words "or commonwealth country" omitted by Act 66 of 1993, s. 3 (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4227&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it appears to`
  line `any magistrate that a person within the local limits of his jurisdiction, is a fugitive criminal of a`
  line `foreign State ^1`
  line `* * * , he may, if he thinks fit, issue a warrant for the arrest of that person on such`
  line `information and on such evidence as would, in his opinion, justify the issue of a warrant if the offence`
  line `of which the person is accused or has been convicted had been committed within the local limits of`
  line `his jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) The magistrate shall forthwith report the issue of a warrant under sub-section (1) to the`
  line `Central Government and shall forward the information, and the evidence or certified copies thereof to`
  line `that Government.`
  line
  line `(3) A person arrested on a warrant issued under sub-section (1) shall not be detained for more than`
  line `three months unless within that period the magistrate receives from the Central Government an order`
  line `made with reference to such person under section 5.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (4228)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Receipt in evidence of exhibits, depositions and other documents and authentication thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4228&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any proceedings against a fugitive criminal of a foreign State ^1* * * under this`
  line `chapter, exhibits and depositions (whether received or taken in the presence of the person against`
  line `whom they are used or not) and copies thereof and official certificates of facts and judicial documents`
  line `stating facts may, if duly authenticated, be received as evidence.`
  line
  line `(2) Warrants, depositions or statements on oath, which purport to have been issued or taken by`
  line `any court of Justice outside India or copies thereof, certificates of, or judicial documents stating the`
  line `facts of conviction before any such court shall be deemed to be duly authenticated if--`
  line
  line `(a) the warrant purports to be signed by a judge, magistrate or officer of the State ^2* * * where`
  line `the same was issued or acting in or of such State ^2* * *;`
  line
  line `(b) the depositions of statements or copies thereof purport to be certified, under the hand of a`
  line `judge, magistrate or officer of the State ^2`
  line `* * * where the same were taken, or acting in or for such`
  line `State ^2* * *, to be original depositions or statements or to be true copies thereof, as the case may`
  line `require ;`
  line
  line `(c) the certificate of, or judicial document stating the fact of, a conviction purports to be`
  line `certified by a judge, magistrate or officer of the State ^2* * * where the conviction took place or`
  line `acting in or for such State ;`
  line
  line `(d) the warrants, depositions, statements, copies, certificates and judicial documents, as the`
  line `case may be, are authenticated by the oath of some witness or by the official seal of a Minister of`
  line `the State ^2* * * where the same were ^3* * * issued, taken or given.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or commonwealth country" omitted by Act 66 of 1993, s. 3 (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  line
  line `2. The words "or country" omitted by Act 66 of 1993, s. 3 (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  line
  line `3. The word "respectively" omitted by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (4229)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Chapter not to apply to commonwealth countries to which Chapter III applies.`
  content `Nothing contained in this Chapter shall apply to fugitive criminals ^1* * * to which Chapter III applies.`
  footnotes `1. The words "of a commonwealth country" omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4229&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (4230)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Application of Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4230&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Chapter shall apply only to any such ^1[foreign state] to`
  line `which, by reason of an extradition arrangement entered into with that ^2[State], it may seem expedient`
  line `to the Central Government to apply the same.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such application shall be by notified order, and the Central Government may, by the`
  line `same or any subsequent notified order, direct that this Chapter and Chapters I, IV and V shall, in`
  line `relation to any such ^1[foreign State], apply subject to such modifications, exceptions, conditions and`
  line `qualifications as it may think fit to specify in the order for the purpose of implementing the`
  line arrangement.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "commonwealth country" (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for "country" (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (4231)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Liability of fugitive criminals from foreign States to be apprehended and returned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "commonwealth country" (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4231&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Where a fugitive criminal of any ^10[foreign State] to which this Chapter applies is found in`
  line `India, he shall be liable to be apprehended and returned in the manner provided by this Chapter to that`
  line `^10[foreign State].`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (4232)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Endorsed and provisional warrants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4232&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `A fugitive criminal may be apprehended in India`
  line `under an endorsed warrant or a provisional warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (4233)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Endorsed warrant for apprehension of fugitive criminal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "commonwealth country" (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4233&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Where a warrant for the`
  line `apprehension of a fugitive criminal has been issued in any ^1[foreign State] to which this Chapter`
  line `applies and such fugitive criminal is, or is suspected to be, in India, the Central Government may, if`
  line `satisfied that the warrant was issued by a person having lawful authority to issue the same, endorse`
  line `such warrant in the manner prescribed, and the warrant so endorsed shall be sufficient authority to`
  line `apprehend the person named in the warrant and to bring him before and magistrate in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (4234)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Provisional warrant for apprehension of fugitive criminal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 66 of 1993, s. 3, for "commonwealth country" (w.e.f. 18-12-1993)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4234&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any magistrate may issue`
  line `a provisional warrant for the apprehension of a fugitive criminal from any ^1[foreign State] to which`
  line `this Chapter applies who is, or is suspected to be, in or on his way to India, on such information and`
  line `under such circumstances as would, in his opinion, justify the issue of a warrant, if the offence of`
  line `which the fugitive criminal is accused or has been convicted had been committed within his`
  line `jurisdiction and such warrant may be executed accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) A magistrate issuing a provisional warrant shall forthwith send a report of the issue of the`
  line `warrant together with the information or a certified copy thereof to the Central Government, and the`
  line `Central Government may, if it thinks fit, discharge the person apprehended under such warrant.`
  line
  line `(3) A fugitive criminal apprehended on a provisional warrant may, from time to time, be`
  line `remanded for such reasonable time, not exceeding seven days at any one time, as under the`
  line `circumstances seems requisite for the production of an endorsed warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (4235)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Dealing with fugitive criminal when apprehended.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4235&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the magistrate, before whom a`
  line `person apprehended under this Chapter is brought, is satisfied on inquiry that the endorsed warrant for`
  line `the apprehension of the fugitive criminal is duly authenticated and that the offence of which the`
  line `person is accused or has been convicted is an extradition offence, the magistrate shall commit the`
  line `fugitive criminal to prison to await his return and shall forthwith send to the Central Government a`
  line `certificate of the committal.`
  line
  line `(2) If on such inquiry the magistrate is of opinion that the endorsed warrant is not duly`
  line `authenticated or that the offence of which such person is accused or has been convicted is not an`
  line `extradition offence, the magistrate may, pending the receipt of the orders of the Central Government,`
  line `detain such person in custody or release him on bail.`
  line
  line `(3) The magistrate shall report the result of his inquiry to the Central Government and shall`
  line `forward together with such report any written statement which the fugitive criminal may desire to`
  line `submit for the consideration of that Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (4236)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Return of fugitive criminal by warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 66 of 1993, s. 3, for "commonwealth country" (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4236&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, at any time after a`
  line `fugitive criminal has been committed to prison under this Chapter, issue a warrant for the custody and`
  line `removal to the ^1[foreign State] concerned of the fugitive criminal and for his delivery at a place and to`
  line `a person to be named in the warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (4237)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Mode of requisition or form of warrant for the surrender or return to India of accused or convicted person who is in a foreign State or Commonwealth country.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4237&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `19. Mode of requisition or form of warrant for the surrender or return to India of accused`
  line `or convicted person who is in a foreign State ^1* * *.--(1) A requisition for the surrender of a person`
  line `accused or convicted of an extradition offence committed in India and who is or is suspected to be, in`
  line `any foreign State ^2* * * to which Chapter III does not apply, may be made by the`
  line `Central Government--`
  line
  line `(a) to a diplomatic representative of that State ^3* * * at Delhi; or`
  line
  line `(b) to the Government of that State ^3* * * through the diplomatic representative of India in`
  line `that State`
  line `^3* * *;`
  line
  line `and if neither of these modes is convenient, the requisition shall be made in such other mode as is`
  line `settled by arrangement made by the Government of India with that State ^3* * *.`
  line
  line `(2) A warrant issued by a magistrate in India for the apprehension of any person who is, or is`
  line `suspected to be, in any ^4[foreign State] to which Chapter III applies shall be in such form as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or commonwealth country" omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  line
  line `2. The words "or a commonwealth country" omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  line
  line `3. The words "or country" omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f.18-12-1993).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 66 of 1993, s. 3, for "commonwealth country" (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (4238)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Conveyance of accused or convicted person surrendered or returned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. The words "or commonwealth country" omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4238&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Any person`
  line `accused or convicted of an extradition offence who is surrendered or returned by a foreign State ^1*** may, under the warrant of arrest for his surrender or return issued in such State or country, be brought`
  line `into India and delivered to the proper authority to be dealt with according to law.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (4239)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Accused or convicted person surrendered or returned by foreign State not to be tried for certain offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for section 21 (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4239&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `^1[21. Accused or convicted person surrendered or returned by foreign State not to be tried`
  line `for certain offences.--Whenever any person accused or convicted of an offence, which, if committed`
  line `in India would be an extradition offence, is surrendered or returned by a foreign State, such person`
  line `shall not, until he has been restored or has had an opportunity of returning to that State, be tried in`
  line `India for an offence other than--`
  line
  line `(a) the extradition offence in relation to which he was surrendered or returned; or`
  line
  line `(b) any lesser offence disclosed by the facts proved for the purposes of securing his surrender`
  line `or return other than an offence in relation to which an order for his surrender or return could not`
  line `be lawfully made; or`
  line
  line `(c) the offence in respect of which the foreign State has given its consent.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (4240)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Liability of fugitive criminals to be arrested and surrendered or returned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. The words "or commonwealth country" omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4240&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line Every
  line `fugitive criminal of a foreign State ^1* * * shall, subject to the provisions of this Act, be liable to be`
  line `arrested and surrendered or returned, whether the offence in respect of which the surrender or return is`
  line `sought was committed before or after the commencement of this Act, and whether or not a court in`
  line `India has jurisdiction to try that offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (4241)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Jurisdiction as to offences committed at sea or in air.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4241&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Where the offence in respect of`
  line `which the surrender or return of a fugitive criminal is sought was committed on board any vessel on`
  line `the high seas or any aircraft while in the air outside India or the Indian territorial waters which comes`
  line `into any port or aerodrome of India, the Central Government and any magistrate having jurisdiction in`
  line `such port or aerodrome may exercise the powers conferred by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (4242)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Discharge of person apprehended if not surrendered or returned within two months.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. The words "or country" omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4242&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `If a fugitive criminal who, in pursuance of this Act, has been committed to prison to await his`
  line `surrender or return to any foreign State ^1* * * is not conveyed out of India within two months after`
  line `such committal, the High Court, upon application made to it by or on behalf of the fugitive criminal`
  line `and upon proof that reasonable notice of the intention to make such application has been given to the`
  line `Central Government, may order such prisoner to be discharged unless sufficient cause is shown to the`
  line contrary.
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (4243)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Release of persons arrested on bail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for "the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)" (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4243&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `In the case of a person who is a fugitive criminal`
  line `arrested or detained under this Act, the provisions of ^1[the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974)] relating to bail shall apply in the same manner as they would apply if such person were`
  line `accused of committing in India the offence of which he is accused or has been convicted, and in`
  line `relation to such bail, the magistrate before whom the fugitive criminal is brought shall have, as far as`
  line `may be, the same powers and jurisdiction as a court of session under that Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (4244)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Abetment of extradition offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 66 of 1993, s. 14 (w.e.f 18-12-1993)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4244&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `A fugitive criminal who is accused or convicted of`
  line `abetting ^1[, conspiring, attempting to commit, inciting or participating as an accomplice in the`
  line `commission of] any extradition offence shall be deemed for the purposes of this Act to be accused or`
  line `convicted of having committed such offence and shall be liable to be arrested and surrendered`
  line accordingly.
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (4245)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Lawfulness of, and retaking on escape from, custody under warrants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4245&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful`
  line `for any person to whom a warrant is directed for the apprehension of a fugitive criminal to hold in`
  line `custody and convey the person mentioned in the warrant to the place named in the warrant, and if`
  line `such person escapes out of any custody to which he may be delivered in pursuance of such warrant, he`
  line `may be re-taken as a person accused of an offence against the law of India may be re-taken upon an`
  line escape.
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (4246)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Property found on fugitive criminal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4246&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Everything found in the possession of a fugitive`
  line `criminal at the time of his arrest which may be material as evidence in proving the extradition offence`
  line `may be delivered up with the fugitive criminal on his surrender or return, subject to the rights, if any,`
  line `of third parties with respect thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (4247)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power of Central Government to discharge any fugitive criminal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4247&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `If it appears to the`
  line `Central Government that by reason of the trivial nature of the case or by reason of the application for`
  line `the surrender or return of a fugitive criminal not being made in good faith or in the interests of justice`
  line `or for political reasons or otherwise, it is unjust or inexpedient to surrender or return the fugitive`
  line `criminal, it may, by order, at any time stay any proceedings under this Act and direct any warrant`
  line `issued or endorsed under this Act to be cancelled and the person for whose arrest the warrant has been`
  line `issued or endorsed to be discharged.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (4248)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Simultaneous requisitions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4248&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `If requisitions for the surrender of a fugitive criminal are`
  line `received from more than one foreign State ^1`
  line `***, the Central Government may, having regard to the`
  line `circumstances of the case, surrender the fugitive criminal to such State or country as that Government`
  line `thinks fit`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or commonwealth country or from any foreign State and any commonwealth country" omitted by s. 15, ibid.`
  line `(w.e.f 18-12-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (4249)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Restrictions on surrender.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4249&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] A fugitive criminal shall not be surrendered or returned to`
  line `a foreign State ^2***.--`
  line
  line `(a) if the offence in respect of which his surrender is sought is of a political character or if he`
  line `proves to the satisfaction of the magistrate or court before whom he may be produced or of the`
  line `Central Government that the requisition or warrant for his surrender has, in fact, been made with a`
  line `view to try or punish him for an offence of a political character;`
  line
  line `(b) if prosecution for the offence in respect of which his surrender is sought is according to`
  line `the law of that State ^3*** barred by time;`
  line
  line `^4[(c) unless provision is made by that law of the foreign State or in the extradition treaty with`
  line `the foreign State that the fugitive criminal shall not be determined or tried in that State for an`
  line `offence other than--`
  line
  line `(i) the extradition offence in relation to which he is to be surrendered or returned;`
  line
  line `(ii) any lesser offence disclosed by the facts proved for the purposes of securing his`
  line `surrender or return other than an offence in relation to which an order for his surrender or`
  line `return could not be lawfully made; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the offence in respect of which the Central Government has given its consent;]`
  line
  line `(d) if he has been accused of some offence in India, not being the offence for which his`
  line `surrender or return is sought, or is undergoing sentence under any conviction in India until after`
  line `he has been discharged, whether by acquittal or on expiration of his sentence or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(e) until after the expiration of fifteen days from the date of his being committed to prison by`
  line `the magistrate.`
  line
  line `^5[(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the offence specified in the Schedule shall not be`
  line `regarded as offences of a political character.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government having regard to the extradition treaty made by India with any`
  line `foreign State may, by notified order, add or omit any offence from the list given in the Schedule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 31 re-numbered as sub-section (1) of that section by s. 16, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  line
  line `2. The words "or commonwealth country" omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f.18-12-1993).`
  line
  line `3. The words "or country" omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 66 of 1993, s. 16 (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (4250)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Sections 29 and 31 to apply without any modification thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. The words "or commonwealth country" omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4250&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `to the contrary contained in section 3 or section 12, the provisions of sections 29 and 31 shall apply`
  line `without any modification to every foreign State ^1***.`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (4251)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Act not to affect the Foreigners Act, 1946.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4251&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall affect the provisions`
  line `of the Foreigners Act, 1946 (31 of 1946), or any order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (4252)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Extra territorial jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for section 34 (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4252&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `^1[34. Extra territorial jurisdiction.--An extradition offence committed by any person in a`
  line `foreign State shall be deemed to have been committed in India and such person shall be liable to be`
  line `prosecuted in India for such offence].`
obj_root_law_sections_34_a:
  sectionId (4253)
  sectionNo 34A
  orderNo 35
  title `Prosecution on refusal to extradition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for section 34 (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4253&sectionno=34A&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_34_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[34A. Prosecution on refusal to extradition.--Where the Central Government is of the opinion`
  line `that a fugitive criminal cannot be surrendered or returned pursuant to a request for extradition from a`
  line `foreign State, it may, as it thinks fit, take steps to prosecute such fugitive criminal in India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34_b:
  sectionId (4254)
  sectionNo 34B
  orderNo 36
  title `Provisional arrest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for section 34 (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4254&sectionno=34B&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_34_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[34B. Provisional arrest.--(1) On receipt of an urgent request from a foreign State for the`
  line `immediate arrest of a fugitive criminal, the Central Government may request the Magistrate having`
  line `competent jurisdiction to issue a provisional warrant for the arrest of such fugitive criminal.`
  line
  line `(2) A fugitive criminal arrested under sub-section (1) shall be discharged upon the expiration of`
  line `sixty days from the date of his arrest if no request for his surrender or return is received within the`
  line `said period.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34_c:
  sectionId (4255)
  sectionNo 34C
  orderNo 37
  title `Provision of life imprisonment for death penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for section 34 (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4255&sectionno=34C&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_34_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[34C. Provision of life imprisonment for death penalty.--Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in any other law for the time being in force, where a fugitive criminal, who has committed an`
  line `extradition offence punishable with death in India, is surrendered or returned by a foreign State on the`
  line `request of the Central Government and the laws of that foreign State do not provide for a death`
  line `penalty for such an offence, such fugitive criminal shall be liable for punishment of imprisonment for`
  line `life only for that offence.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (4256)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 38
  title `Notified orders and notifications to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4256&sectionno=35&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Every notified order made`
  line `or notification issued under this Act shall, as soon as may be after it is made or issued, be laid before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (4257)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4257&sectionno=36&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form in which a requisition for the surrender of a fugitive criminal may be made;`
  line
  line `(b) the form in which a warrant for the apprehension of any person in a ^1[foreign State] to`
  line `which Chapter III applies may be made;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which any warrant may be endorsed or authenticated under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) the removal of fugitive criminals accused or in custody under this Act and their control`
  line `and maintenance until such time as they are handed over to the persons named in the warrant as`
  line `entitled to receive them;`
  line
  line `(e) the seizure and disposition of any property which is the subject of, or required for proof of,`
  line `any alleged offence to which this Act applies;`
  line
  line `(f) the form and manner in which or the channel through which a magistrate may be required`
  line `to make his report to the Central Government under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or ^2[in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive session aforesaid], both Houses agree in making`
  line `any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so however`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "commonwealth country" (w.e.f. 18-12-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f 15-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (4258)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 40
  title `Repeals and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487&sectionId=4258&sectionno=37&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00009_196234_1517807322487
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Indian Extradition Act, 1903 (15 of 1903), and any law`
  line `corresponding thereto in force at the commencement of this Act in the territories which, immediately`
  line `before the 1st day of November, 1956, were comprised in Part B States and the North East Frontier`
  line `Agency and Tuensang District (Extradition) Regulation, 1961 (3 of 1961), are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Extradition Acts, 1870 to 1932 (33 and 34 Vict. c. 52; 36 and 37 Vict. c. 60; 6 Edw. 7, c.`
  line `15; 22 and 23 Geo. 5, c. 39, 44 and 45 Vict. c. 69) and the Fugitive Offenders Act, 1881, in so far as`
  line `they apply to and operate as part of the law of India, are hereby repealed.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
